 And the best viewing spots are virtually in California's back yard: The Big Island of Hawaii and the southern Baja California peninsula.
 The Dei Rossis were in. "We are so excited," Pamela Dei Rossi said. "We had given up." Though travel arrangements are now tough to come by, some opportunities remain.
 Hawaii and Baja are the prime spots, because -- statistically at least -- they offer the best chance of cloudless skies.
